        <div class="pros">
          <h4>Pros</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Highly customizable for dietary restrictions</li>
            <li>Grocery lists auto-populate efficiently</li>
            <li>Generous free tier with plenty of recipes</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cons">
          <h4>Cons</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Cannot easily import your own recipes on the free tier</li>
            <li>Limited advanced macro tracking</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="review-card">
      <div class="review-header">
        <h3>2. Eat This Much</h3>
        <span class="review-tier">Freemium</span>
      </div>
      <div class="review-body">
        <div class="pros">
          <h4>Pros</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Incredible automatic meal planning based on macro targets</li>
            <li>Great for weight loss and bodybuilding</li>
            <li>Reduces decision fatigue completely</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cons">
          <h4>Cons</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Premium version is relatively expensive</li>
            <li>Some generated meals can be repetitive or simplistic</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="review-card">
      <div class="review-header">
        <h3>3. Paprika</h3>
        <span class="review-tier">Paid (One-time)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="review-body">
        <div class="pros">
          <h4>Pros</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Best-in-class web recipe scraper</li>
            <li>One-time purchase model (no subscription fatigue)</li>
            <li>Excellent offline functionality and syncing</li>
