      <div class="review-header">
        <h3>6. Whisk (Samsung Food)</h3>
        <span class="review-tier">100% Free</span>
      </div>
      <div class="review-body">
        <div class="pros">
          <h4>Pros</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Completely free to use with no premium paywalls</li>
            <li>Excellent community features and shared recipe boxes</li>
            <li>Integrates with many grocery delivery services</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cons">
          <h4>Cons</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>UI can sometimes feel overwhelming with community features</li>
            <li>Less emphasis on strict macro tracking</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="review-card">
      <div class="review-header">
        <h3>7. MealPrepPro</h3>
        <span class="review-tier">Paid Subscription</span>
      </div>
      <div class="review-body">
        <div class="pros">
          <h4>Pros</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Designed specifically for batch cooking and meal prep</li>
            <li>Scales recipes perfectly based on your calorie needs</li>
            <li>Great instructional videos for each recipe</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cons">
          <h4>Cons</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>No free version available</li>
            <li>Android app historically lags behind the iOS experience</li>
          </ul>
