      <h3>Best for Macro Tracking & Weight Loss</h3>
      <p><strong>Eat This Much</strong> is the undisputed champion here. By allowing you to input exact macronutrient and caloric goals, it automates the hardest part of dieting by generating a complete day of meals that perfectly hit your targets.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cat-box">
      <h3>Best for Recipe Hoarders</h3>
      <p><strong>Paprika</strong> stands out for its legendary recipe scraping tool. If you have hundreds of bookmarks to various food blogs, Paprika will cleanly strip away the life stories and ads, leaving you with just the ingredients and instructions in a beautifully organized digital cookbook.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cat-box">
      <h3>Best Free App</h3>
      <p><strong>Whisk (now Samsung Food)</strong> offers a premium-level experience entirely for free. You can import recipes, generate shopping lists, and collaborate with family members without ever hitting a paywall.</p>
